                <h2>Exploring Quartz as an Alternative</h2>

                <p>While granite remains a top choice, many homeowners are also discovering the benefits of <strong>quartz countertops</strong>. Quartz is an engineered stone that offers a non-porous surface, meaning it never needs sealing and is highly resistant to stains and bacteria. It's also available in a wider range of consistent colors and patterns, making it easier to achieve a specific design look.</p>

                <p>For homeowners who love the appearance of natural stone but prefer a lower-maintenance option, quartz is an excellent choice. Griffin Quartz is a leader in both granite and quartz fabrication, giving you the flexibility to explore both materials with a single trusted partner. Browse our <a href="../kitchen-bath">kitchen and bath portfolio</a> to see the possibilities.</p>

